  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and slice the <strong>red onions</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onions</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 10-12 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-mushroom-pitta-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> (skin on) into wedges</p><p>Add the wedges to a large baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up </p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the wedges are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-mushroom-pitta-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong>and cut the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p><p>Combine the <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a small bowl</p><p>Add the juice of the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and mix to form a paste – this is your <strong>peri peri paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-mushroom-pitta-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Brush the <strong>peri peri </strong>paste evenly all over the <strong>portobello mushrooms </strong>until fully coated – these are your <strong>coated mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-mushroom-pitta-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onions have caramelised, remove them from the pan and set aside, reserve the pan</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated mushrooms</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through – these are your <strong>peri peri mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-mushroom-pitta-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, wash the <strong>gem lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and finely shred</p><p>Slice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es] </span></strong>into rounds</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-mushroom-pitta-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> pittas</strong> to the tray with the sweet potato wedges and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-mushroom-pitta-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>warmed pittas </strong>in half and spread a dollop of <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> inside each,  then stuff with the <strong>peri peri mushrooms</strong>, <strong>caramelised onions</strong>, <strong>shredded lettuce </strong>and <strong>tomato rounds</strong> – these are your <strong>peri peri mushroom pittas</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>peri peri mushroom pittas</strong> with the <strong>sweet potato wedges</strong> and any <strong>remaining shredded lettuce</strong> and <strong>tomato rounds</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
